originalText.text: I had my first appointment with Dr. Levy today and I left feeling not only heard but like I have an ally when it comes to my physical and mental health. It was the first time since IPads were invented that a doctor took the time to sit me down in their own personal office and looked me in the eye while getting to know me as a person as whole. I was so much more comfortable because I wasn’t sitting on a paper covered examination table staring at the doctor’s back while they typed. He is the epitome of the type of doctor that takes the time to listen their patients and fully explore their needs. Doctors like him are quickly fading due to insurance companies so I highly recommend him to anyone seeking quality and personalized healthcare.

originalText.text: We went there for visa examination for my parents. It was easy to take the appointment. From reception to examiner , everyone is very nice , polite. We went earlier than the appointment time and we didn’t have to wait . If you are coming from other state , please keep in mind that you might have to pay a good amount of money for parking. We parked our car for little bit over 3 hours and we paid 64$ including taxes. For the health examination we paid $800 . It’s too expensive but no other option as we came from CT.

originalText.text:
Went there for a medical exam for Australian Immigration. Booking the appointment was easy but they don't send a confirmation message or email which was a bit inconvenient.
Staff at the facility was great. Everyone starting from the receptionist to the examiner was extremely polite. Cost for the exam was high but this was the only option near Boston.

originalText.text:
1. I called Dr. Levy's CELL PHONE on a work holiday, and he answered. He politely told me he could fit me in first thing the next day and even told me where to park.  2. The people who took my information were quick and professional.   3. The Doctor who examined me was wonderful and the nurse practitioner was the same. They were both super thoughtful and great to work with.   4. Dr. Levy stepped into the exam room to introduce himself. He was so kind and funny. Honestly, my new favorite doctor.    5. Several days later I followed up to see if they can expedite the process, by sending my information to immigration. The obliged and responded to my email within minutes.

Overall: Incredible people, incredible service, and easily the best experience I've had with a doctor.
